<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880824-0045 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Ranger Oil Ltd. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ICG RGO </CO><IN> PET LNG TNM </IN><TEXT>   Toronto-based Inter-City Gas Corp. said it acquired 3.2 million additional shares of Ranger Oil Ltd., raising the company's stake in Ranger's 74.6 million common shares outstanding to 13.7% from 9.5%.    Inter-City, which disclosed its initial stake in the Calgary, Alberta-based oil and gas producer Monday, said previously that it wants to combine its oil and gas assets with those of Ranger and is pursuing talks on the subject. Ranger and Inter-City officials couldn't be reached for comment.    Inter-City, which also owns a large natural gas utility and makes heating and cooling equipment, said it acquired the additional Ranger shares privately. The purchase raised Inter-City's holdings in Ranger to more than 10.2 million of its common shares outstanding. In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Ranger closed at $6, unchanged. </TEXT></DOC>